                            <comment id="12859932" author="stack" created="Thu, 22 Apr 2010 18:11:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That&apos;d be fine.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There is also the mechanism whereby if count of HLogs &amp;gt; some configurable amount, we start flushing memstore that holds oldest edits.  This works in some regard but not well enough in your case?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12859938" author="stack" created="Thu, 22 Apr 2010 18:19:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It seems that the current mechanism of flushing the oldest memstores is not enough going by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-2236&quot; title=&quot;Upper bound of outstanding WALs can be overrun; take 2 (take 1 was hbase-2053)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-2236&quot;&gt;HBASE-2236&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12860013" author="kannanm" created="Thu, 22 Apr 2010 21:05:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Stack: Thanks for pointing out. I missed the &quot;hbase.regionserver.maxlogs&quot; control that HBae already has. So, this shouldn&apos;t be a serious concern in that case. I&apos;ll close out this issue. We should still keep &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-2236&quot; title=&quot;Upper bound of outstanding WALs can be overrun; take 2 (take 1 was hbase-2053)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-2236&quot;&gt;HBASE-2236&lt;/a&gt; open to see if we can do better about not violating &quot;hbase.regionserver.maxlogs&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
